President Donald J. Trump hosted French President Emmanuel Macron for a working lunch at the official residence of the United States Ambassador to Belgium. The meeting marked their first in-person engagement following their initial telephone call on May 9. President Trump urged President Macron to meet the NATO defense spending pledge and focus on counterterrorism. He thanked President Macron for France's leadership in counterterrorism efforts in Africa. Both leaders emphasized the importance of defeating ISIS in Iraq and Syria. President Trump also discussed his recent travels to Saudi Arabia and Israel, expressing hope for Middle East peace. They committed to maintaining and strengthening the alliance between the United States and France on various vital issues.